, the only country where specimens of this species have been collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,978,2013]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1230,1256]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Description</emphasis>
. Length: approximately 
<quantity box="[621,758,1231,1257]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" unit="mm" value="2.05" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="1.8">1.8‒2.3 mm</quantity>
(HT 
<quantity box="[822,914,1231,1257]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="24" pageNumber="125" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
). Color: black, scutellum with blue iridescent reflections, dorsellum black with blue reflections. Legs: coxae black, hind femora black or brown, pro and meso femora and tibiae brown, lighter distad and on inner surfaces, with weak blue reflections, tarsi brown. Antennae: scape brown, lighter distad, pedicel and flagellum brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,978,2013]" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
Head: (
<figureCitation box="[281,446,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Figs 10B, 10C</figureCitation>
) in frontal view quadrate, slightly wider than high, HW/HH approximately 1.2, sparsely setose to smooth; in dorsal view weakly transverse (
<figureCitation box="[753,857,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
), width same or slightly greater than twice length, HW/HL 2.0–2.1; wider than pronotum, HW/PW approximately 1.3. Frontal carina: absent. Scrobal cavity: shallow; weak round swelling originating from between median and lateral ocelli extend towards eye margin. Ocelli: large; forming a wide triangle, POL about twice distance between posterior and anterior ocelli; POL very long,&gt;2.5× OOL. Vertex: rounded behind; smooth, interocellar region with long groove originating from occiput to anterior ocellus (
<figureCitation box="[246,347,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
, arrow); occiput with median furrow delimited below vertex, with costulae. Outer orbits: smooth, strong costulae behind. Inner orbits: in lateral view, nearly parallel to inner eye margin; smooth. Malar space: short, about 0.2× eye height, MS/EH approximately 0.2; malar sulcus distinct; very weakly coriarious (
<figureCitation box="[1217,1319,1663,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
). Clypeus: weakly transverse, wider than high, CW/ 
<collectingCountry box="[614,652,1699,1725]" name="Switzerland" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">CH</collectingCountry>
approximately 1.7–1.8, trapezoidal, lateral sulci weak and straight or weakly rounded, weakly divergent; epistomal sulcus straight or weakly concave, same strength as lateral sulci, only slightly extended ventrad; lower margin convex. Supraclypeal area: subquadrate, 0.7–0.8× 
<collectingCountry box="[1206,1248,1771,1797]" name="Switzerland" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">CH</collectingCountry>
. Antenna: scape length approximately 0.5× EH; anellus length approximately 0.1× PL; F1 subquadrate, shorter than pedicel, F1L/PL approximately 0.6–0.7, F2 subquadrate, F3–F7 transverse; clava 4-segmented, with distinct terminal button.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,978,2013]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1437,151,1113]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">
Mesosoma (
<figureCitation box="[337,626,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">Figs 10A, 10D, 10E, 10F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[638,690,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="23.[151,255,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-19@23.[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 11. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒E, P. yemenensis: A, mesosoma, dorsal view; B, head, dorsal view, male; C, lower face sculpture male; D, scape, male; E, aedeagus, male, DCD Slide 2251, ventral view; F‒K, P. houbaraensis: F, mesosoma, dorsal view; G, head, dorsal view, male; H, lower face sculpture, male; I, scape, male; J, scape, male; K, aedeagus, male, dorsal view [A: Holotype, ROME159199; B‒E: Paratype, ROME159193; F: Holotype, ROME159089; G‒I: Paratype, ROME159087; J and K: Paratype, ROME159086]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223069/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="125">11A</figureCitation>
): length approximately 1.3× maximum width. Pronotum in dorsal view: short, about 0.25× length of mesoscutum, PN/MSC 0.2–0.3; shorter along midline, 0.5‒0.6× length laterad; anterior margin sharp, the first row of punctures slightly lower; without flange on lateral panel of pronotum at the level of mesothoracic spiracle. Lateral panel of pronotum: slightly wider than prepectus, LPP/PPT approximately 1.2–1.3; flat, with 3 rows of punctures and wide coriarious interspaces dorsad, ventrad with wide coriarious patch; anterior margin slightly rounded; posterior margin ventrad grooved, with row of alveolae. Prepectus (
<figureCitation box="[1316,1424,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
): narrow; nearly indistinguishable from pronotum, without distinct suture; ventral strap long (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1338,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
, arrow), with row of alveolae; central area smooth, with foveae along dorsal and posterior margins. Femoral depression: nearly smooth. Midlobe of mesoscutum (
<figureCitation box="[634,743,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="23.[151,255,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-19@23.[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 11. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒E, P. yemenensis: A, mesosoma, dorsal view; B, head, dorsal view, male; C, lower face sculpture male; D, scape, male; E, aedeagus, male, DCD Slide 2251, ventral view; F‒K, P. houbaraensis: F, mesosoma, dorsal view; G, head, dorsal view, male; H, lower face sculpture, male; I, scape, male; J, scape, male; K, aedeagus, male, dorsal view [A: Holotype, ROME159199; B‒E: Paratype, ROME159193; F: Holotype, ROME159089; G‒I: Paratype, ROME159087; J and K: Paratype, ROME159086]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223069/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
): without transverse tubercle; punctures rounded to weakly angulate, with wide and coriarious interspaces. Lateral lobe of mesoscutum: smooth dorsad; coriarious-punctate laterad. Scutellum: about as long as mesoscutum, SC/MSC approximately 1.1; posterior margin smoothly rounded; punctures rounded to weakly angulate, with wide and coriarious interspaces. Axilla: punctate dorsad, imbricate below. Axillula: short triangular lobe, shorter than width at base, smooth. Propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[1164,1270,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 10E</figureCitation>
): length along midline about 0.3× width of propodeum; submedian area imbricate, with weak groove along median carina; weakly imbricate laterad; plicae incomplete laterad, delimited ventrad by plicae, dorsad by transverse band of foveae; propodeal spiracle margin narrowly foveate ventrad; nucha rugulose. Fore wing (
<figureCitation box="[1054,1153,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
): postmarginal vein long, 0.8‒0.9× length of marginal vein, 1.4‒1.6× length of stigmal vein; stigmal vein with weak uncus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,1113]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Metasoma: petiole short with large smooth to weakly rugulose raised scale (10E, arrow); Gt2 smooth, posterior margin weakly concave at middle; Gt3 smooth.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,1113]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
Male. Length: approximately 
<quantity box="[531,613,691,717]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7mm</quantity>
. Color, structure, and sculptures similar to female except as follows: Head (
<figureCitation box="[160,264,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="23.[151,255,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-19@23.[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 11. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒E, P. yemenensis: A, mesosoma, dorsal view; B, head, dorsal view, male; C, lower face sculpture male; D, scape, male; E, aedeagus, male, DCD Slide 2251, ventral view; F‒K, P. houbaraensis: F, mesosoma, dorsal view; G, head, dorsal view, male; H, lower face sculpture, male; I, scape, male; J, scape, male; K, aedeagus, male, dorsal view [A: Holotype, ROME159199; B‒E: Paratype, ROME159193; F: Holotype, ROME159089; G‒I: Paratype, ROME159087; J and K: Paratype, ROME159086]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223069/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
): in dorsal view quadrate. Ocelli: larger. Malar space: shorter, with stronger coriarious sculpture (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="23.[151,255,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-19@23.[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 11. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒E, P. yemenensis: A, mesosoma, dorsal view; B, head, dorsal view, male; C, lower face sculpture male; D, scape, male; E, aedeagus, male, DCD Slide 2251, ventral view; F‒K, P. houbaraensis: F, mesosoma, dorsal view; G, head, dorsal view, male; H, lower face sculpture, male; I, scape, male; J, scape, male; K, aedeagus, male, dorsal view [A: Holotype, ROME159199; B‒E: Paratype, ROME159193; F: Holotype, ROME159089; G‒I: Paratype, ROME159087; J and K: Paratype, ROME159086]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223069/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Scape (
<figureCitation box="[306,412,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="23.[151,255,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-19@23.[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 11. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒E, P. yemenensis: A, mesosoma, dorsal view; B, head, dorsal view, male; C, lower face sculpture male; D, scape, male; E, aedeagus, male, DCD Slide 2251, ventral view; F‒K, P. houbaraensis: F, mesosoma, dorsal view; G, head, dorsal view, male; H, lower face sculpture, male; I, scape, male; J, scape, male; K, aedeagus, male, dorsal view [A: Holotype, ROME159199; B‒E: Paratype, ROME159193; F: Holotype, ROME159089; G‒I: Paratype, ROME159087; J and K: Paratype, ROME159086]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223069/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
): about 0.5× EH; weakly stout, length about 4.7× width above radicle; strongly expanded distad, about 1.2× width above radicle; punctures covering about 0.4× scape length, with slightly wide interspaces. Mesosoma: more elongate, length approximately 1.4× maximum width. Gt3: weakly imbricate dorsad. Aedeagus: with paired lateral spines (
<figureCitation box="[447,549,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="23.[151,255,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-19@23.[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 11. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒E, P. yemenensis: A, mesosoma, dorsal view; B, head, dorsal view, male; C, lower face sculpture male; D, scape, male; E, aedeagus, male, DCD Slide 2251, ventral view; F‒K, P. houbaraensis: F, mesosoma, dorsal view; G, head, dorsal view, male; H, lower face sculpture, male; I, scape, male; J, scape, male; K, aedeagus, male, dorsal view [A: Holotype, ROME159199; B‒E: Paratype, ROME159193; F: Holotype, ROME159089; G‒I: Paratype, ROME159087; J and K: Paratype, ROME159086]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223069/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 11K</figureCitation>
, arrow).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="126" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,1113]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,906,932]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The following combination of characters will distinguish 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yoo and Darling" authorityYear="2021" box="[963,1117,907,932]" class="Insecta" family="Perilampidae" genus="Perilampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yemenensis">
<emphasis box="[963,1117,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">P. yemenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the other species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1905" box="[151,243,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Perilampidae" genus="Perilampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">
<emphasis box="[151,243,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">P. tristis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group: postmarginal vein longer than stigmal vein (
<figureCitation box="[920,1020,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
), indistinct suture between prepectus and pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[322,425,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
), strongly imbricate submedian area of propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[1010,1110,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 10E</figureCitation>
), mesonotum with coriarious interspaces (
<figureCitation box="[292,394,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="23.[151,255,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-19@23.[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 11. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒E, P. yemenensis: A, mesosoma, dorsal view; B, head, dorsal view, male; C, lower face sculpture male; D, scape, male; E, aedeagus, male, DCD Slide 2251, ventral view; F‒K, P. houbaraensis: F, mesosoma, dorsal view; G, head, dorsal view, male; H, lower face sculpture, male; I, scape, male; J, scape, male; K, aedeagus, male, dorsal view [A: Holotype, ROME159199; B‒E: Paratype, ROME159193; F: Holotype, ROME159089; G‒I: Paratype, ROME159087; J and K: Paratype, ROME159086]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223069/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
), weakly bluish iridescence on scutellum, coriarious malar region, which is stronger in male (
<figureCitation box="[159,264,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-20@22.[180,1407,180,1875]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒F, P. yemenensis: A, habitus, lateral view; B, head, dorsal view; C, lower face sculpture; D, prepectus; E, propodeum; F, fore wing venation. G‒L, P. houbaraensis: G, habitus, lateral view; H, head, dorsal view; I, lower face sculpture; J, prepectus; K, propodeum; L, fore wing venation. [A‒F: Holotype, ROME159199; G‒L: Holotype, ROME159089]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223065/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Figs 10C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[275,323,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="23.[151,255,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-19@23.[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 11. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒E, P. yemenensis: A, mesosoma, dorsal view; B, head, dorsal view, male; C, lower face sculpture male; D, scape, male; E, aedeagus, male, DCD Slide 2251, ventral view; F‒K, P. houbaraensis: F, mesosoma, dorsal view; G, head, dorsal view, male; H, lower face sculpture, male; I, scape, male; J, scape, male; K, aedeagus, male, dorsal view [A: Holotype, ROME159199; B‒E: Paratype, ROME159193; F: Holotype, ROME159089; G‒I: Paratype, ROME159087; J and K: Paratype, ROME159086]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223069/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">11C</figureCitation>
), and slightly stout male scape with large punctures covering slightly less than 0.5 scape length (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="23.[151,255,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-19@23.[192,1396,180,1843]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 11. Perilampus yemenensis and P. houbaraensis. A‒E, P. yemenensis: A, mesosoma, dorsal view; B, head, dorsal view, male; C, lower face sculpture male; D, scape, male; E, aedeagus, male, DCD Slide 2251, ventral view; F‒K, P. houbaraensis: F, mesosoma, dorsal view; G, head, dorsal view, male; H, lower face sculpture, male; I, scape, male; J, scape, male; K, aedeagus, male, dorsal view [A: Holotype, ROME159199; B‒E: Paratype, ROME159193; F: Holotype, ROME159089; G‒I: Paratype, ROME159087; J and K: Paratype, ROME159086]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5223069" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5223069/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
